cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically visual correspondence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel attention mechanism to optimize the trade-off between discriminativeness and spatial accuracy, which falls under the scope of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely category. The paper also uses deep neural networks, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The proposed method involves optimizing the receptive field sizes, which is a concept related to neural networks and signal processing, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on optical flow and semantic matching benchmarks, which are tasks related to multimedia and image processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
